content: When I took leadership of AWS Config, the prevailing internal narrative was that customer churn was due to pricing. The team and stakeholders were convinced we needed to significantly reduce prices. Inherited the Control Tower team focused incorrectly on recreating the full AWS user experienceâ€”resulting in complexity, delayed releases, and customer dissatisfaction. * Detailed Customer Segmentation Analysis: I initiated a deep usage-data study across customer segments. We explicitly tested the hypothesis by offering deeply discounted pricing (up to 50% off) to assess price sensitivity. * Feature Gap Analysis: Discovered through structured interviews that churned customers primarily sought specific inventory management features or capabilities from competitive services like Wiz, rather than lower costs. * Focused Value Proposition: Shifted strategy away from generalized AWS UI replication towards a focused, unique valueâ€”creating a centralized, reusable "Control Catalog." * Cross-team Collaboration: Worked closely with partner teams to identify common governance requirements, standardizing these controls centrally. * Analytical depth and rigor * Customer-centric research * Strategic decision-making backed by evidence * Clear strategic reframing * Cross-organizational alignment * Customer-focused value definition * After repositioning messaging around governance/audit rather than cost, we halted churn almost immediately and regained several key customers. * Internal data showed governance/audit customers had >85% retention rates, while churn was driven primarily by customers seeking specific missing inventory features. ðŸ“Œ 5. title: JWCC Government Contract Turnaround
content: AWS discovered very late that a high-visibility JWCC (Joint Warfighter Cloud Capability) U.S. government contract bid faced failure due to a partner team committing to a non-viable third-party solution that couldn't deliver within required timelines. * Rapid Technical Re-architecting: Quickly engaged with the third-party vendor, negotiating modifications to their product to make it a feasible short-term hosted solution. * Strategic Negotiation: Reduced original cost by negotiating a new contract at approximately 1/6 the initial estimate, saving millions in projected expenses. * Proactive Transition Plan: Established a clear technical roadmap to smoothly transition to native AWS solutions post-initial delivery. * High-pressure negotiation skills * Crisis and risk management * Strategic flexibility and rapid innovation * Won the JWCC contract, avoiding reputational damage from public failure. * Successfully transitioned the customer to native AWS solutions at renewal, as customer feedback explicitly preferred AWS-managed solutions over third-party managed offerings.

title: Challenging Customer Relationship â€“ Domain Controls
content: A major enterprise customer escalated severe frustrations around AWS governance practices, providing unclear and broad complaints, risking significant dissatisfaction and reputational damage. * Structured Customer Workshops: Facilitated detailed multi-day sessions mapping the customerâ€™s current governance workflows and pain points, uncovering their core issueâ€”absence of "domain controls," which prevented unauthorized account creation. * Strategic Customer Trust Building: Took the unusual step of transparently sharing our detailed roadmap, risks, and progress monthly, building trust and credibility over time. * High-level conflict resolution * Detailed process mapping and problem-solving * Exceptional stakeholder relationship management * After delivering the domain controls feature, the customer's sentiment dramatically improved, and they evolved into one of AWSâ€™s closest and most trusted enterprise governance partners. * Their CIO later cited our transparency and engagement as a "model partnership" in internal communications, leading to smoother interactions on subsequent issues.

title: Automated Reasoning (Weirwood) Integration into AWS Config
content: AWS Config had recurring stability and accuracy issues from human-authored governance controlsâ€”slow to develop and error-prone. * Technical Risk & Innovation: Decided strategically to reallocate engineers and budget toward integrating automated reasoning technology ("Weirwood") to write provably correct controls. * Investment Justification: Made explicit trade-off, prioritizing long-term gain over immediate technical debt remediation. * Strategic technical innovation * Bold decision-making under uncertainty * Ability to manage high-technical risk for outsized returns * Improved control development speed from ~60 days to ~2 days per control. * Doubled annual control-output capacity, significantly improving AWS Configâ€™s operational reliability and customer trust.

title: AWS Config Infrastructure and Partnership Reset
content: Inherited AWS Config with accumulated technical debt, unreliable stability/security, and strained relationships with partner teams. * Investment in Infrastructure: Explicitly prioritized foundational improvements in security, reliability, and partner integration features, despite short-term revenue impact. * Relationship Restoration: Led intensive reconciliation and trust-building efforts with partner teams. * Deep infrastructure expertise * Strategic prioritization * Inter-team conflict resolution * Stability improvements reduced production incidents by 70% within the first year. * Directly contributed critical infrastructure and features essential to successful AWS security flagship launch at re:Inforce.
